                        STATIC KEYWORDS

1) Static is keyword decalred to member variables and member function, never declared to class.

2)Static property (member variable and member function) work as a common property for all objects.

3) Static property accessed by:
            scope resolution operator                          
                     \                  member variable
                      \                 /
             classname::property name
                                        \
                                        member functions.

4) Static keywords never declared to virtual function.
5) Static functions never over ride.

            non Static:                             member variable
                                                        /
                                        object variable.
                                                        \
                                                    member function


            static:                             member variables
                                                    /
                                        classname::
                                                    \
                                                member function

6) Static variables must be initilized at outside class before used.
    syntax:
            datatype classname:: static variable=value;

